{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01TucvqiJD1StexFeo6F1RsK","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `cluster.initial_master_nodes` is set to all 3 nodes. This is causing a problem - with a running cluster (not initial bootstrap), the `cluster.initial_master_nodes` setting is only used for initial bootstrapping. But after the cluster loses quorum (2 of 3 master nodes are gone), it needs to reform.\n\nThe issue is that es-cluster-0 needs a minimum quorum of 2 nodes to elect a master (with initial_master_nodes having 3 entries). Actually wait, in ES 7.x, the master election requires a majority of the `cluster.initial_master_nodes`. \n\nOnce a cluster is formed, `cluster.initial_master_nodes` becomes informational only—the cluster relies on its internal metadata and voting configuration to determine which nodes can vote. With only es-cluster-0 remaining, it can't achieve quorum and is likely stuck waiting for the other master nodes to return. To recover a single-node cluster that's lost quorum, I'd need to use a specific recovery mechanism rather than just restarting.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":745,"cache_read_input_tokens":41935,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":745},"output_tokens":32,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5b5a42fb-dee8-4f2d-8a98-4796cae8b0c0","uuid":"8aa4663a-9d0f-443c-9c79-909a617da01b","request_id":"req_011CcQaHyXZaeojpH1zjHNV6"}
